This message is for families of Grand View students that have prescription medication stored in the Health Office.

The State Department of Education recommends that parents pick up their child’s medications next week.

LaDonna Walls, the Grand View Health Aide will be in her office on Wednesday, March 25 from 7:30-9:00am. This aligns with the daily grab-&-go meal service times and guidelines.

Please call Mrs. Walls at 918-456-5131 extension 505 BEFORE you get to the school. She will gather your child’s medication and bring them out to the grab-&-go awning next to the cafeteria upon your arrival.

post_text: Shortly after State Superintendent Hofmeister's conference call on Friday afternoon, a national emergency related to the COVID-19 Coronavirus was declared. Some items discussed during the Superintendent's call will be impacted through additional funding and resources and by the change in strategy. We will watch for changes in the CDC's recommended practices. In the meantime we will work to clean the school and school equipment, consider alternative dining and recess schedules, develop ways to provide more space during classroom and PE activities, and review schedules for any events that assemble more than 100 individuals. Finally, those traveling on cruises, out of country, and to other states will need to notify the school as classes resume. If those areas are considered hotspots at that time, we will expect a 14-day self-quarantine.
text: Shortly after State Superintendent Hofmeister's conference call on Friday afternoon, a national emergency related to the COVID-19 Coronavirus was declared. Some items discussed during the Superintendent's call will be impacted through additional funding and resources and by the change in strategy. We will watch for changes in the CDC's recommended practices. In the meantime we will work to clean the school and school equipment, consider alternative dining and recess schedules, develop ways to provide more space during classroom and PE activities, and review schedules for any events that assemble more than 100 individuals. Finally, those traveling on cruises, out of country, and to other states will need to notify the school as classes resume. If those areas are considered hotspots at that time, we will expect a 14-day self-quarantine.

School starts tomorrow. Breakfast will be served beginning at 7:20. First bell is at 7:45 and classes begin at 7:50.

Drop off and pickup procedures will primarily remain the same: Absolutely no drop off or pickup along the fence. The safest drop off for elementary and middle school students is the loop on the northeast corner of campus. Elementary students can be picked up there at the end of the day. Although a crossing guard is utilized daily, the gravel lot should only be used for dropping off older students in the morning. That is also the afternoon pickup location for middle school students and those elementary students that have middle school siblings. The southwest gate ELC will be… More

post_text:
Who: 6th-8th Grade GV Academic Team Members
What: Tournament of Champions Online Qualifier
When: Friday, March 8, 2018 from 9AM – 4PM
Where: Ms. Prag’s Classroom (please enter through front doors)
Why: Placing 1st, 2nd, or 3rd qualifies the student for the Tournament of Champs State

Competition at Redlands Community College, El Reno, OK on Sat. Apr. 6, 2019.
Students will test in the following subjects: mathematics, language arts, science, social studies, humanities, and current events. Students will have 50 minutes to take each online test.The number of questions vary based on subject. Please arrive BY 8:30 AM, in order to get
logged into the computers and prepare to begin tests. The school will provide lunch, but students may bring snacks. After testing, we will meet parents/guardians in front of the office.

Results should be available by early April.
